In article <trimmC6sH9u.H1D@netcom.com> trimm@netcom.com (Trimm Industries) writes:
>I'm afraid y'all are missing the point - the NSA *wants* the clipper to be
>secure, algorithmically speaking.  So long as they have easy access to the
>keys to our private communications, why would they want anyone to be able
>to break it?  

If the NSA actually used the same chip in all of their top-secret
communications, *that* would make me feel a lot better for its
security.  That's a good idea anyway... it would prevent the NSA and
other government agencies from holding secrets back from the rest of
the government.

